# Runtime: require image digest pin

Container image tags are mutable. `docker.io/miniforge/task-runner:latest`
on Monday is not the same image as Tuesday. A workflow that runs against
a tag has no reproducibility story — re-running the same execution plan
produces different artifacts; evidence bundles point at content that
might no longer exist.

Per N6 (Evidence & Provenance), execution plans MUST carry a
content-addressed image reference. Reject any plan whose
`:image-digest` is a tag-style reference instead of a `sha256:` digest.

## Detection

Inspect the execution plan's `:image-digest`. Match against the
fully-qualified reference patterns:

- `:pass` — `<registry>/<repo>@sha256:<64-hex>` (digest-pinned)
- `:violation` — `<registry>/<repo>:<tag>` (tag-pinned)
- `:violation` — short-name reference without a registry segment

```clojure
(let [ref (:image-digest plan)]
  (cond
    (re-matches #".+@sha256:[a-f0-9]{64}$" ref)        :pass
    (re-matches #"[a-z0-9.-]+\.[a-z0-9.-]+/[^/]+:.+" ref) :violation/tag
    :else                                              :violation/short-name))
```

## Enforcement

- **Action:** `:hard-stop`
- **Phases:** `:plan`, `:release`
- **Scope:** every execution plan; no opt-out

## Why no opt-out

Reproducibility and the evidence-bundle audit trail are non-negotiable
for governed execution. A workflow that legitimately needs the latest
build of an image should resolve the tag to a digest at plan-build
time and record the resolution; running against the tag itself defeats
the audit story.

## Interaction with `runtime/images.edn`

The default image references in `runtime/images.edn` use tags today
(e.g. `docker.io/miniforge/task-runner-clojure:latest`) because the
images aren't yet published with stable digests. This rule does NOT
fire on those defaults — it fires on the resolved `:image-digest` that
miniforge writes into the execution plan. The plan-build phase is
responsible for resolving the tag to a digest before the executor sees
it.

## Spec reference

- N11-delta §5 (image references must be fully qualified)
- N11-delta §6 `:runtime/require-image-digest-pin`
- N6 (evidence & provenance — digest pinning is the audit primitive)
